ers/Top-Players/David-Nalbandian.aspx</ref>\u2013\n | [[Juan M\u00f3naco]] (2004<ref>http://www.tennis-ontheline.com/aw/aw040223.htm</ref>&ndash;2011<ref>http://sportifi.com/news/Juan-Monaco-Hires-Gaston-Etlis-as-New-Tennis-Coach-653550.html</ref>)\n }}\n| CoachSinglesTitles    = 12(R)-1(Moya)-1(N)-3(Mon.)=17(total)\n| CoachDoublesTitles    = 3(R)-2(Mon.)=5(total)\n| CoachTournamentRecord = {{unbulleted list\n | 1998 Rome, Miami, Indian Wells Masters (Rios)\n | 1998 [[Grand Slam Cup]] (Rios)\n | 1999 Hamburg Masters (Rios)\n | 1998 Australian Open (Rios doubles)\n | 1999 Monte Carlo Masters (Rios doubles)\n }}\n| CoachingAwards        =\n| CoachingRecords       =\n}}\n\n'''Luis Lobo''' (born 9 November 1970) is a retired professional male [[tennis]] player from [[Argentina]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Luis Lobo: Profile|publisher=Association of Tennis Professionals|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Tennis/Players/Lo/L/Luis-Lobo.aspx|accessdate=26 January 2011}}</ref> who won the gold medal in the men's doubles competition at the [[1995 Pan American Games]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Pan American Games History|publisher=United States Tennis Association|url=http://www.usta.com/Pro-Tennis/Olympics-Pan-Am/Pan-American/Information/21398_Pan_American_Games_History/|accessdate=26 January 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JLg7rFwC?url=http://www.usta.com/Pro-Tennis/Olympics-Pan-Am/Pan-American/Information/21398_Pan_American_Games_History/|archivedate=3 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe reached his career high doubles ranking, World No. 12, on 21 July 1997.<ref>{{cite web|title=Luis Lobo: Rankings History|publisher=Association of Tennis Professionals|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/Tennis/Players/Lo/L/Luis-Lobo.aspx?t=rh|accessdate=26 January 2011}}</ref> He is currently a coach, and has worked with players including Spain's [[Carlos Moy\u00e0]] and Argentina's [[Juan M\u00f3naco]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography: Monaco, Juan (ARG)|publisher=International Tennis Federation|url=http://www.itftennis.com/procircuit/players/player/profile.aspx?playerid=100003032|accessdate=26 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Career finals==\n===Doubles: 20 (12 wins, 8 losses)===\n{|\n|-valign=top\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" \n|- \n|'''Legend'''\n|- style=\"background:#f3e6d7;\"\n| Grand Slam (0)\n|- style=\"background:#ffffcc;\"\n| Tennis Masters Cup (0)\n|- style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"\n| ATP Masters Series (1)\n|- style=\"background:#d4f1c5;\" \n| ATP Championship Series (2)\n|-\n| ATP Tour (9)\n|}\n|\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\" \n|- \n|'''Titles by surface'''\n|-\n| Hard (2)\n|-\n| Clay (10)\n|-\n| Grass (0)\n|-\n| Carpet (0)\n|}\n|}\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n!style=\"width:40px\"|Result\n!style=\"width:30px\" class=\"unsortable\"|W/L \n!style=\"width:60px\"|Date\n!style=\"width:160px\"|Tournament\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:150px\"|Partner\n!style=\"width:150px\"|Opponents\n!style=\"width:110px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Win\n| 1.\n| Oct 1994\n| [[ATP Athens|Athens]], Greece\n| Clay\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Javier S\u00e1nchez (tennis)|Javier S\u00e1nchez]]\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Cristian Brandi]] <br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Federico Mordegan]]\n| 5\u20137, 6\u20131, 6\u20134\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss\n| 1.\n| Jan 1995\n| [[ATP Auckland|Auckland]], New Zealand\n| Hard\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Javier S\u00e1nchez (tennis)|Javier S\u00e1nchez]]\n| {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Grant Connell]] <br> {{flagicon|USA}} [[Patrick Galbraith]]\n| 6\u20134, 6\u20133\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss\n| 2.\n| Mar 1995\n| [[Tennis Channel Open|Scottsdale]], U.S.\n| Hard\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} Javier S\u00e1nchez\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Trevor Kronemann]] <br> {{flagicon|AUS}} [[David Macpherson (tennis)|David Macpherson]]\n| 4\u20136, 6\u20133, 6\u20134\n|- style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|