{"title_page": "When Hope Calls", "text_new": "{{short description|Spin-off of When Calls the Heart}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = When Hope Calls\n| image = \n| caption = \n| genre = {{Plainlist|\n*[[dramatic programming|Family Drama]]\n*[[Western (genre)|Western]]\n}}\n| based_on = ''[[When Calls the Heart]]''\n| creator = Alfonso H. Moreno\n| writer = \n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n*Morgan Kohan \n*Jocelyn Hudon\n*RJ Hatanaka\n*Greg Hovanessian\n*[[Wendy Crewson]]\n}}\n| country = {{Plainlist|\n*Canada\n*United States\n}}\n| language = English\n| composer = \n| num_seasons = 1<!-- Update only when a new season begins airing -->\n| num_episodes = 10<!-- Update only when a new episode airs -->\n| list_episodes = \n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n*Alfonso H. Moreno\n*Brian Bird\n*[[Brad Krevoy]]\n*[[Susie Belzberg Krevoy]]\n*[[Michael Landon Jr.]]\n*Amanda Phillips Atkins\n*Jimmy Townsend\n*Eric Jarboe\n*[[Mike Rohl]]\n}}\n| producer = David Anselmo\n| location = [[Powassan]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| runtime = 40\u201343 mins.\n| company =\n| network =  [[Hallmark Movies Now]]<br>([[Crown Media]])<br/>[[Hallmark Channel]]\n| picture_format =\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2019|8|30}} (Hallmark Movies Now)<br/>{{Start date|2020|2|23}} (Hallmark Channel)\n| last_aired = {{End date|present}}\n| related = \n| website = https://www.hallmarkchannel.com/when-hope-calls\n}}\n\n'''''When Hope Calls''''' is an American [[drama]] television series. It premiered on August 30, 2019 as the inaugural original programming on [[Hallmark Movies Now]], the [[Hallmark Channel]]'s digital streaming service. The series is a [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of the network's ''[[When Calls the Heart]]'', which is based on the [[Janette Oke#Canadian West series|''Canadian West'' book series]] by [[Janette Oke]].\n\n==Premise==\nThe series follows Lillian and Grace, originally introduced in ''[[List of When Calls the Heart episodes#Special (2018)|When Calls the Heart: The Greatest Christmas Blessing]]'', as two orphaned sisters, who were separated when Lillian was seven and Grace was five. The two reunite as adults and open an orphanage in a small northwest town.<ref name= \"PressRel\"/> The [[Historical period drama|period piece]] is set in 1916 in the [[Western Canada|western Canadian]] town of Brookfield.<ref name=\"Teaser\">[https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/life/entertainment/a28660118/when-hope-calls-premiere-date-cast-spoilers/ ''When Hope Calls: Premier, Date, Cast Spoilers'']; TV Guide online; accessed August 18, 2019</ref> Mountie Gabriel has a romantic interest in Lillian. Chuck, a rancher turned veterinarian, is the object of Grace's flirtations, much to the dismay of his dubious mother, Tess Stewart.<ref name=\"Teaser\"/>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n\n===Main===\n*Morgan Kohan as Lillian \"Lily\" Walsh, Grace's older sister who was adopted at a young age and separated from Grace\n*Jocelyn Hudon as Grace Bennett, Lillian's younger sister who grew up in an orphanage\n*RJ Hatanaka as Constable Gabriel \"Gabe\" Kinslow, the local Mountie in town\n*Greg Hovanessian as Charlie \"Chuck\" Stewart,  Tess' son, and a rancher and the town veterinarian\n*[[Wendy Crewson]] as Tess Stewart, Chuck's mother, who owns the big local ranch\n\n===Recurring===\n*Isaak Bailey as Christian\n*Michael Copeman as Kenneth \"Ken\" Newsome, a miserly old man\n*[[Neil Crone]] as Ronnie Stewart, Chuck's uncle and Tess's brother-in-law who runs the local hotel\n*Liam MacDonald as Vincent\n*[[Kate Moyer]] as Sophia\n*Riley O'Donnell as Helen\n*Kalinka Petrie as Lucille \"Lucie\" Clay, Chuck's childhood friend who may be romantically interested in him\n*[[Kim Roberts (actress)|Kim Roberts]] as Pearl Mayfair\n*Elizabeth Saunders as Eleanor Winters\n*Simon Webster as Fred\n*Ava Weiss as Mary Louise \n*Hanneke Talbot as Margaret \"Maggie\" Parsons, the town nurse who is newly arrived to Brookfield\n*[[Jefferson Brown]] as Joseph \"Joe\" Moody, the owner of Brookfield's general store\n*[[Drew Nelson (actor)|Drew Nelson]] as Daniel Olsen \n*[[Jonathan Potts]] as Benjamin \"Ben\" Mendelson\n*Josh Reich as Ben's son\n*Carrie Schiffler as Ben's wife\n*Naomi Sagbien as Alice Mayfair\n*Kelly Boegel as Ruth\n*[[Marshall Williams]] as Samuel \"Sam\" Tremblay, a drifter into town who works as a handyman for Lillian at the orphanage\n\n===Guest stars===\n*[[Pascale Hutton]] as Rosemary \"Rosie\" LeVeaux Coulter, an acquaintance of Grace's from Hope Valley (in \"From the Ashes\")\n*[[Kavan Smith]] as Leland \"Lee\" Coulter, another acquaintance of Grace's from Hope Valley (in \"From the Ashes\")\n*Kevin McGarry as Nathan Grant, the Mountie from Hope Valley (in \"The Search\", \"House in Order\", and \"Where Hope Goes\")\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table\n|background =#72A0C1|overall=|title=|titleR=<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/when-hope-calls/listings/ |title=Shows A\u2013Z \u2013 ''When Hope Calls'' on HMN |publisher=[[The Futon Critic]] |access-date=September 8, 2019}}</ref> |director= |writer= |airdate=|released=1 |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 1\n |Title = New Hope\n |DirectedBy = [[Michael Rohl|Mike Rohl]]\t\n |WrittenBy = Alfonso Moreno\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|8|30}}\n |ShortSummary = Having newly set up their orphanage in Brookfield, sisters Lillian and Grace face unwelcoming neighbors, especially Tess Stewart who has unresolved issues with Lillian's family. Constable Gabriel Kinslow reacquaints himself with the sisters after returning to town and is immediately charmed by Lillian. Meanwhile, Chuck, the town's veterinarian and Tess's son, helps Grace, when the cow she purchased from his mother fails to produce milk, and is impressed by Grace's tenacity. Despite their disagreements, the town bands together when a crisis strikes during the grand opening of a new hotel and puts lives, including Lillian's, at risk. This disaster helps Lillian and Grace gain some acceptance but creates a mystery for Gabriel to solve.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 2\n |Title = From the Ashes\n |DirectedBy = Mike Rohl\n |WrittenBy = Larry Bambrick\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|8|30}}\n |ShortSummary = Brookfield rebuilds after a devastating fire, and visitors from [[When Calls the Heart|Hope Valley]] lend a hand. Lillian and Grace welcome Rosemary and Lee Coulter, who bring lumber and support. Gabriel investigates the cause of the fire, and, when evidence points to two orphans, Lillian begins to doubt her qualifications to run an orphanage. Tess's tumultuous history with Lillian's family complicates the mutual attraction between Grace and Chuck. Having lost his store in the fire, Joe considers moving. Meanwhile, nurse Maggie Parsons arrives in town, and Tess continues to feud with one of her neighbors over missing livestock.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 3\n |Title = Out of the Past\n |DirectedBy = Bradley Walsh\n |WrittenBy = Derek Thompson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|6}}\n |ShortSummary = New evidence points Gabriel toward a suspect in the town fire, leading him to hunt for a fugitive. Grace takes a second job to make money for the orphanage, hoping to use the funds to help make the lives of the children in her care better than hers was growing up. Lillian tries to mend fences with Tess. Maggie settles into her job at the infirmary.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 4\n |Title = Lost and Found\n |DirectedBy = Bradley Walsh\n |WrittenBy = Sara Snow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|13}}\n |ShortSummary = Lillian searches for an orphan's family member and hopes for the same success she had when she found Grace. She journeys to [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police|Mountie]] headquarters with Gabriel, and, while she searches through records, he meets with the bank robber who tried to kill him. Despite having no impact on his jail sentence, the bank robber claims that he is accused of stealing more money than he actually stole. Back in Brookfield, Grace and Chuck grow closer, but Tess orchestrates a scenario to extinguish their romantic spark. Maggie tries to help Joe with an old shoulder injury and soon realizes that guilt about the accident that caused it may be preventing him from trying to heal.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 5\n |Title = A House United\n |DirectedBy = [[Don McBrearty]]\n |WrittenBy = David Barlow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|20}}\n |ShortSummary = When a government worker comes to inspect the orphanage, Lillian and Grace attempt to measure up. Although they use creativity and community to address issues at the orphanage, the true test arises when the inspector questions events from Grace's past. Gabriel and Chuck help repair the orphanage's roof and work alongside Sam, a struggling [[Prospecting|prospector]] offering handyman services in exchange for room and board. Gabriel seems to be jealous over Sam's closeness to Lillian, while Chuck hopes to restore his blossoming relationship with Grace. Meanwhile, Tess puts her endeavor to buy a truck on hold when Ronnie needs her help.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 6\n |Title = The Search\n |DirectedBy = Don McBrearty\n |WrittenBy = Sara Snow & Larry Bambrick\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|27}}\n |ShortSummary = When a train robber is spotted near Brookfield, Lillian and Grace attempt to keep their orphans safe. Despite her initial instinct to trust Sam, Lillian second-guesses herself when the description of the train robber \u2013 and the caution of Gabriel Kinslow \u2013 casts doubts on his character. Gabriel helps Constable Nathan Grant, in town from Hope Valley, in hunting down the fugitive. Chuck stays at the orphanage as a protective measure and to spend more time with Grace. Tess interviews candidates for a new foreman but hopes that Chuck will eventually decide to run the family ranch. Meanwhile, Maggie makes an interesting discovery at the infirmary.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 7\n |Title = Surprise\n |DirectedBy = [[T. W. Peacocke]]\n |WrittenBy = David Barlow & Sara Snow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|4}}\n |ShortSummary = Hoping to replace Grace's painful birthday memories with happy new ones, Lillian rallies the orphans and friends from town to plan a party, but Grace does extra work at the restaurant on the night of the party. Meanwhile, Chuck takes Fred, one of the orphans, under his wing at the ranch, and Tess softens her steely demeanor when she sees the joy Fred experiences around the animals. Setting off on another possibly dangerous mission, Gabriel pursues a witness to the bank robbery who claims that powerful people used the robbery to cover up fraud. Sam and Lillian spend time together preparing a special birthday gift for Grace, during Gabriel's absence, and arouses his jealousy when he returns.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 8\n |Title = Its About a Girl\n |DirectedBy = T. W. Peacocke\n |WrittenBy = Alfonso Moreno\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|11}}\n |ShortSummary = Though Lillian locates Helen's grandfather, Helen struggles to remember the facts about her past that she needs to know in order to prove her identity. Determined to see the reunion through, Lillian turns to Sam and her friends in town for support. A friend from Grace's past encourages her to follow her dream of moving to New York, while Chuck urges her to stay. Gabriel's investigation into the suspected bank fraud raises questions about how Ronnie funded his hotel, and Tess tries to protect Ronnie when his less-than-legal hotel funding gets him in trouble with debtors. Meanwhile, Maggie helps a visitor of Brookfield searching for healthy living.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 9\n |Title = House in Order\n |DirectedBy = [[Megan Follows]]\n |WrittenBy = David Barlow & Larry Bambrick\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|18}}\n |ShortSummary = A reporter comes to Brookfield to do a story on Tess' late husband; Gabriel's investigation hits close to home; Chuck and Grace face an impasse in their relationship.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n }}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 10\n |Title = Where Hope Goes\n |DirectedBy = Megan Follows\n |WrittenBy = Alfonso Moreno & Sara Snow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|25}}\n |ShortSummary = Lillian and Grace make a difficult choice in order to do what's best for one of their orphans; Gabriel hopes to get his man before Lillian, or anyone else, gets hurt; Chuck realizes that it is time to share his true feelings. Gabriel and Nathan keep their eye on their suspects. Gabriel feels they may go after Lillian, so he reluctantly asks for Sam's help to protect her. Grace prepares to accompany Helen to England to be reunited with her grandfather; she worries about leaving town and Chuck while they are in the midst of an argument. Unaware of her travel plans, Chuck accompanies Lucie on a cattle drive for his mother.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n}}\n\n==Production==\n''When Hope Calls'' is a spin-off of the long running [[prime time]] series ''When Calls the Heart''.<ref name=\"HMN\"/> Primary filming is at [[Powassan]], [[Ontario]], Canada.<ref name=\"Teaser\"/> It is executive produced by Alfonso Moreno,<ref name=\"Teaser\"/> Brian Bird, [[Brad Krevoy]], Susie Belzberg Krevoy, [[Michael Landon Jr.]], Amanda Phillips Atkins, Jimmy Townsend, and Eric Jarboe.\n\nConfirmation of the project, the Hallmark Network's inaugural streaming series, was announced February 9, 2019 as part of [[Crown Media]] Family Networks' bi-annual Television Critics Association Winter Press Tour.<ref name=\"HMN\">[https://www.spoilertv.com/2018/07/when-hope-calls-when-calls-heart-gets.html ''Hallmark Movies Now's First Original Series 'When Hope Calls' Premieres August 2019'']; spoilerTV.com; accessed February 20, 2019</ref><ref name=\"Mitovitch\">{{cite news | last1=Mitovich| first1=Matt Webb| title=Good Witch Renewed for Season 5, When Calls the Heart Gets Spinoff| url=https://tvline.com/2018/07/26/good-witch-renewed-season-5-hallmark/| accessdate=March 1, 2019| work=TVLine| date=July 26, 2018}}</ref><ref name= \"PressRel\">{{cite press release | url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/02/09/hallmark-movies-nows-first-original-series-when-hope-calls-premieres-august-2019-86202/20190209hallmark03/| title=Hallmark Movies Now's First Original Series, \"When Hope Calls,\" Premieres August 2019| date=February 9, 2019| publisher=[[Crown Media Holdings]]| agency=[[The Futon Critic]] via press release from The Hallmark Channel| location=[[Pasadena, California]]| access-date=March 5, 2019}}</ref> ''When Hope Calls'' premiered in back-to-back double episodes on August 30, 2019 on the Hallmark Movies Now network [[subscription TV|digital streaming service]].<ref name=\"Teaser\"/>\n\nAs of February 2020, the first season is re-airing on [[Hallmark Channel]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title}}\n*[https://www.hallmarkchannel.com/when-calls-the-heart/videos/preview-when-hope-calls ''Preview: When Hope Calls'']; Hallmark Channel.\n\n[[Category:Hallmark Channel original programming]]\n[[Category:Period family drama television series]]\n[[Category:Television series produced in Vancouver]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Spin-off of When Calls the Heart}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = When Hope Calls\n| image = \n| caption = \n| genre = {{Plainlist|\n*[[dramatic programming|Family Drama]]\n*[[Western (genre)|Western]]\n}}\n| based_on = ''[[When Calls the Heart]]''\n| creator = Alfonso H. Moreno\n| writer = \n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n*Morgan Kohan \n*Jocelyn Hudon\n*RJ Hatanaka\n*Greg Hovanessian\n*[[Wendy Crewson]]\n}}\n| country = {{Plainlist|\n*Canada\n*United States\n}}\n| language = English\n| composer = \n| num_seasons = 1<!-- Update only when a new season begins airing -->\n| num_episodes = 10<!-- Update only when a new episode airs -->\n| list_episodes = \n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n*Alfonso H. Moreno\n*Brian Bird\n*[[Brad Krevoy]]\n*[[Susie Belzberg Krevoy]]\n*[[Michael Landon Jr.]]\n*Amanda Phillips Atkins\n*Jimmy Townsend\n*Eric Jarboe\n*[[Mike Rohl]]\n}}\n| producer = David Anselmo\n| location = [[Powassan]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| runtime = 40\u201343 mins.\n| company =\n| network =  [[Hallmark Movies Now]]<br>([[Crown Media]])<br/>[[Hallmark Channel]]\n| picture_format =\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2019|8|30}} (Hallmark Movies Now)<br/>{{Start date|2020|2|23}} (Hallmark Channel)\n| last_aired = {{End date|present}}\n| related = \n| website = https://www.hallmarkchannel.com/when-hope-calls\n}}\n\n'''''When Hope Calls''''' is an American [[drama]] television series. It premiered on August 30, 2019 as the inaugural original programming on [[Hallmark Movies Now]], the [[Hallmark Channel]]'s digital streaming service. The series is a [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of the network's ''[[When Calls the Heart]]'', which is based on the [[Janette Oke#Canadian West series|''Canadian West'' book series]] by [[Janette Oke]].\n\n==Premise==\nThe series follows Lillian and Grace, originally introduced in ''[[List of When Calls the Heart episodes#Special (2018)|When Calls the Heart: The Greatest Christmas Blessing]]'', as two orphaned sisters, who were separated when Lillian was seven and Grace was five. The two reunite as adults and open an orphanage in a small northwest town.<ref name= \"PressRel\"/> The [[Historical period drama|period piece]] is set in 1916 in the [[Western Canada|western Canadian]] town of Brookfield.<ref name=\"Teaser\">[https://www.goodhousekeeping.com/life/entertainment/a28660118/when-hope-calls-premiere-date-cast-spoilers/ ''When Hope Calls: Premier, Date, Cast Spoilers'']; TV Guide online; accessed August 18, 2019</ref> Mountie Gabriel has a romantic interest in Lillian. Chuck, a rancher turned veterinarian, is the object of Grace's flirtations, much to the dismay of his dubious mother, Tess Stewart.<ref name=\"Teaser\"/>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n\n===Main===\n*Morgan Kohan as Lillian \"Lily\" Walsh, Grace's older sister who was adopted at a young age and separated from Grace\n*Jocelyn Hudon as Grace Bennett, Lillian's younger sister who grew up in an orphanage\n*RJ Hatanaka as Constable Gabriel \"Gabe\" Kinslow, the local Mountie in town\n*Greg Hovanessian as Charlie \"Chuck\" Stewart,  Tess' son, and a rancher and the town veterinarian\n*[[Wendy Crewson]] as Tess Stewart, Chuck's mother, who owns the big local ranch\n\n===Recurring===\n*Isaak Bailey as Christian\n*Michael Copeman as Kenneth \"Ken\" Newsome, a miserly old man\n*[[Neil Crone]] as Ronnie Stewart, Chuck's uncle and Tess's brother-in-law who runs the local hotel\n*Liam MacDonald as Vincent\n*[[Kate Moyer]] as Sophia\n*Riley O'Donnell as Helen\n*Kalinka Petrie as Lucille \"Lucie\" Clay, Chuck's childhood friend who may be romantically interested in him\n*[[Kim Roberts (actress)|Kim Roberts]] as Pearl Mayfair\n*Elizabeth Saunders as Eleanor Winters\n*Simon Webster as Fred\n*Ava Weiss as Mary Louise \n*Hanneke Talbot as Margaret \"Maggie\" Parsons, the town nurse who is newly arrived to Brookfield\n*[[Jefferson Brown]] as Joseph \"Joe\" Moody, the owner of Brookfield's general store\n*[[Drew Nelson (actor)|Drew Nelson]] as Daniel Olsen \n*[[Jonathan Potts]] as Benjamin \"Ben\" Mendelson\n*Josh Reich as Ben's son\n*Carrie Schiffler as Ben's wife\n*Naomi Sagbien as Alice Mayfair\n*Kelly Boegel as Ruth\n*[[Marshall Williams]] as Samuel \"Sam\" Tremblay, a drifter into town who works as a handyman for Lillian at the orphanage\n\n===Guest stars===\n*[[Pascale Hutton]] as Rosemary \"Rosie\" LeVeaux Coulter, a acquaintance of Grace's from Hope Valley (in \"From the Ashes\")\n*[[Kavan Smith]] as Leland \"Lee\" Coulter, another acquaintance of Grace's from Hope Valley (in \"From the Ashes\")\n*Kevin McGarry as Nathan Grant, the Mountie from Hope Valley (in \"The Search\", \"House in Order\", and \"Where Hope Goes\")\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table\n|background =#72A0C1|overall=|title=|titleR=<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/when-hope-calls/listings/ |title=Shows A\u2013Z \u2013 ''When Hope Calls'' on HMN |publisher=[[The Futon Critic]] |access-date=September 8, 2019}}</ref> |director= |writer= |airdate=|released=1 |episodes= \n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 1\n |Title = New Hope\n |DirectedBy = [[Michael Rohl|Mike Rohl]]\t\n |WrittenBy = Alfonso Moreno\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|8|30}}\n |ShortSummary = Having newly set up their orphanage in Brookfield, sisters Lillian and Grace face unwelcoming neighbors, especially Tess Stewart who has unresolved issues with Lillian's family. Constable Gabriel Kinslow reacquaints himself with the sisters after returning to town and is immediately charmed by Lillian. Meanwhile, Chuck, the town's veterinarian and Tess's son, helps Grace, when the cow she purchased from his mother fails to produce milk, and is impressed by Grace's tenacity. Despite their disagreements, the town bands together when a crisis strikes during the grand opening of a new hotel and puts lives, including Lillian's, at risk. This disaster helps Lillian and Grace gain some acceptance but creates a mystery for Gabriel to solve.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 2\n |Title = From the Ashes\n |DirectedBy = Mike Rohl\n |WrittenBy = Larry Bambrick\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|8|30}}\n |ShortSummary = Brookfield rebuilds after a devastating fire, and visitors from [[When Calls the Heart|Hope Valley]] lend a hand. Lillian and Grace welcome Rosemary and Lee Coulter, who bring lumber and support. Gabriel investigates the cause of the fire, and, when evidence points to two orphans, Lillian begins to doubt her qualifications to run an orphanage. Tess's tumultuous history with Lillian's family complicates the mutual attraction between Grace and Chuck. Having lost his store in the fire, Joe considers moving. Meanwhile, nurse Maggie Parsons arrives in town, and Tess continues to feud with one of her neighbors over missing livestock.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 3\n |Title = Out of the Past\n |DirectedBy = Bradley Walsh\n |WrittenBy = Derek Thompson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|6}}\n |ShortSummary = New evidence points Gabriel toward a suspect in the town fire, leading him to hunt for a fugitive. Grace takes a second job to make money for the orphanage, hoping to use the funds to help make the lives of the children in her care better than hers was growing up. Lillian tries to mend fences with Tess. Maggie settles into her job at the infirmary.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 4\n |Title = Lost and Found\n |DirectedBy = Bradley Walsh\n |WrittenBy = Sara Snow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|13}}\n |ShortSummary = Lillian searches for an orphan's family member and hopes for the same success she had when she found Grace. She journeys to [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police|Mountie]] headquarters with Gabriel, and, while she searches through records, he meets with the bank robber who tried to kill him. Despite having no impact on his jail sentence, the bank robber claims that he is accused of stealing more money than he actually stole. Back in Brookfield, Grace and Chuck grow closer, but Tess orchestrates a scenario to extinguish their romantic spark. Maggie tries to help Joe with an old shoulder injury and soon realizes that guilt about the accident that caused it may be preventing him from trying to heal.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 5\n |Title = A House United\n |DirectedBy = [[Don McBrearty]]\n |WrittenBy = David Barlow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|20}}\n |ShortSummary = When a government worker comes to inspect the orphanage, Lillian and Grace attempt to measure up. Although they use creativity and community to address issues at the orphanage, the true test arises when the inspector questions events from Grace's past. Gabriel and Chuck help repair the orphanage's roof and work alongside Sam, a struggling [[Prospecting|prospector]] offering handyman services in exchange for room and board. Gabriel seems to be jealous over Sam's closeness to Lillian, while Chuck hopes to restore his blossoming relationship with Grace. Meanwhile, Tess puts her endeavor to buy a truck on hold when Ronnie needs her help.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 6\n |Title = The Search\n |DirectedBy = Don McBrearty\n |WrittenBy = Sara Snow & Larry Bambrick\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|27}}\n |ShortSummary = When a train robber is spotted near Brookfield, Lillian and Grace attempt to keep their orphans safe. Despite her initial instinct to trust Sam, Lillian second-guesses herself when the description of the train robber \u2013 and the caution of Gabriel Kinslow \u2013 casts doubts on his character. Gabriel helps Constable Nathan Grant, in town from Hope Valley, in hunting down the fugitive. Chuck stays at the orphanage as a protective measure and to spend more time with Grace. Tess interviews candidates for a new foreman but hopes that Chuck will eventually decide to run the family ranch. Meanwhile, Maggie makes an interesting discovery at the infirmary.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 7\n |Title = Surprise\n |DirectedBy = [[T. W. Peacocke]]\n |WrittenBy = David Barlow & Sara Snow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|4}}\n |ShortSummary = Hoping to replace Grace's painful birthday memories with happy new ones, Lillian rallies the orphans and friends from town to plan a party, but Grace does extra work at the restaurant on the night of the party. Meanwhile, Chuck takes Fred, one of the orphans, under his wing at the ranch, and Tess softens her steely demeanor when she sees the joy Fred experiences around the animals. Setting off on another possibly dangerous mission, Gabriel pursues a witness to the bank robbery who claims that powerful people used the robbery to cover up fraud. Sam and Lillian spend time together preparing a special birthday gift for Grace, during Gabriel's absence, and arouses his jealousy when he returns.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 8\n |Title = Its About a Girl\n |DirectedBy = T. W. Peacocke\n |WrittenBy = Alfonso Moreno\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|11}}\n |ShortSummary = Though Lillian locates Helen's grandfather, Helen struggles to remember the facts about her past that she needs to know in order to prove her identity. Determined to see the reunion through, Lillian turns to Sam and her friends in town for support. A friend from Grace's past encourages her to follow her dream of moving to New York, while Chuck urges her to stay. Gabriel's investigation into the suspected bank fraud raises questions about how Ronnie funded his hotel, and Tess tries to protect Ronnie when his less-than-legal hotel funding gets him in trouble with debtors. Meanwhile, Maggie helps a visitor of Brookfield searching for healthy living.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 9\n |Title = House in Order\n |DirectedBy = [[Megan Follows]]\n |WrittenBy = David Barlow & Larry Bambrick\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|18}}\n |ShortSummary = A reporter comes to Brookfield to do a story on Tess' late husband; Gabriel's investigation hits close to home; Chuck and Grace face an impasse in their relationship.\n |LineColor = 72A0C1\n }}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 10\n |Title = Where Hope Goes\n |DirectedBy = Megan Follows\n |WrittenBy = Alfonso Moreno & Sara Snow\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|25}}\n |ShortSummary = Lillian and Grace make a difficult choice in order to do what's 