{"title_page": "Laurie Warder", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox tennis biography\n| name                  = Laurie Warder\n| image                 = \n| caption               = \n| country               = {{AUS}}\n| residence             = \n| birth_date            = {{birth date and age|df=y|1962|10|23}}\n| birth_place           = [[Sydney]], Australia\n| height                = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| turnedpro             = \n| retired               = \n| plays                 = Right-handed\n| careerprizemoney      = [[US$|$]]864,953\n| singlesrecord         = \n| singlestitles         = 0\n| highestsinglesranking = No. 210 (10 August 1987)\n| AustralianOpenresult  = \n| FrenchOpenresult      = \n| Wimbledonresult       = \n| USOpenresult          = \n| Othertournaments      = \n| MastersCupresult      = \n| WCTFinalsresult       = \n| doublesrecord         = \n| doublestitles         = 12\n| highestdoublesranking = No. 12 (12 October 1991)\n| AustralianOpenDoublesresult = '''W''' (1993)\n| FrenchOpenDoublesresult     = QF (1987, 1991, 1992)\n| WimbledonDoublesresult      = QF (1986, 1989)\n| USOpenDoublesresult         = QF (1988)\n}}\n'''Laurie Warder ''' (born 23 October 1962) is a former professional male [[tennis]] player from Australia who specialized in the doubles event. In 1987 he won the doubles title at the [[Australian Open]] partnering compatriot [[Peter Doohan]]. Warder won 12 doubles titles during his career and achieved a highest doubles ranking of No. 12 in October 1991.\n\n==Career finals==\n===Doubles (12 titles, 18 runner-ups)===\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n!style=\"width:55px\"|Result\n!style=\"width:25px\"|No.\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Date\n!style=\"width:200px\"|Tournament\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Partner\n!style=\"width:180px\"|Opponents\n!style=\"width:150px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss\n| 1.